ton shooter Matthew Raymond will stand trial Sept. 30}}</ref>\n|-\n|Salmon Arm Church of Christ shooting\n|April 14, 2019\n|[[Salmon Arm]], [[British Columbia]]\n|1 / 1 / 0\n| Shooting\n|No\n|Matrix Savage Gathergood, 25, was charged with first-degree murder of Gordon Parmenter, aggravated assault and disguise with intent to commit an indictable offence in connection with the shooting on April 15.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/salmon-arm-shooting-charges-1.5098750|title=25-year-old charged with murder after deadly shooting at Salmon Arm church|last=|first=|date=April 15, 2019|website=CBC|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522170801/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/salmon-arm-shooting-charges-1.5098750|archive-date=May 22, 2019|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|Penticton shootings\n|April 15, 2019\n|[[Penticton]], [[British Columbia]]\n|4\n| Long gun\n| No\n|Four people killed in three different locations by a man reported to have used a rifle, and who immediately turned himself in to police.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vancouversun.com/news/local-news/penticton-shootings-live-updates-and-what-we-know-so-far |title = Penticton shootings: Live updates and what we know so far &#124; Vancouver Sun|date = April 17, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2019 Northern British Columbia murders]]\n|July 14-19, 2019\n|[[British Columbia]]\n|3\n| Long gun\n| Yes\n|An Australian and an American tourist were found dead. Five days later, another man was found dead.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.insider.com/british-columbia-murders-missing-teens-link-rcmp-2019-7 |title = 2 murders, a death, and 2 disappearances in a remote, wild part of Canada could all be connected, police say}}</ref> On July 23, the RCMP initiated a country-wide manhunt for the two outstanding suspects.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/ten-days-four-provinces-how-two-b-c-suspected-fugitives-continue-to-evade-rcmp|tit